inputbox-error-no-type:
Used as error message.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Inputbox-error-bad-type}}

inputbox-error-bad-type:
{{doc-important|Don't translate "create", "comment", "search", "search2" and "fulltext"!}}
Used as error message. Parameters:
* $1 - invalid type. Valid types are: "create", "comment", "commenttitle", "search", "fulltext", and "search2"
See also:
* {{msg-mw|Inputbox-error-no-type}}

inputbox-searchfulltext:
Part of the "Inputbox" extension. This message is the text of the button to search the page you typed in the inputbox. This button always goes to the search page, even if the page with the exact name exists.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Search}}
* {{msg-mw|Accesskey-search-fulltext}}
* {{msg-mw|Tooltip-search-fulltext}}
